msgid ""
"You can build Nuclear units when you have the required advance, and the "
"Manhattan Project wonder has been built by any player."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1208 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1915
msgid ""
"On impact, the blast will destroy any unit in an area 3 tiles wide (3x3 "
"squares for rectangular grids), including friendly units. Any city within "
"the blast area loses half its population, and land tiles within the blast "
"area are subject to nuclear fallout, which appears as pollution and "
"contributes to global warming."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1214
msgid ""
"TIP 1:  Nuking the ocean will not generate fallout, and is a most effective "
"(but expensive!!) way of getting rid of enemy ships."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1218
msgid ""
"TIP 2:  You may be involved in a situation where you have invaded an enemy "
"country en masse, but the enemy cities are too strong. Before using a "
"Nuclear unit, assemble a gang of Settlers next to the city and have them "
"ready to fix the fallout on the same turn it occurs!  This minimizes the "
"chance of global warming. Eco-friendly nukes!"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1228 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1935
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2196 data/classic/units.ruleset:1991
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2018 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2090
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2733 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2268
msgid "Diplomat"
msgstr "diplomat"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1259 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2237
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2030 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2057
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2129 data/royale/units.ruleset:2773
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2309
msgid ""
"A Diplomat is an official that carries your dispatches and is authorized to "
"deal with foreign dignitaries. He may also undertake various covert "
"operations with the intent of harming your opponents. Diplomats in your own "
"cities defend them against such actions."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1265 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1972
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2036 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2063
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2135
msgid ""
"Many covert actions may be attempted even in peacetime, but the more "
"aggressive actions will be discovered and cause diplomatic incidents, which "
"can allow Republics and Democracies to break treaties."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1269 data/classic/units.ruleset:2040
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2067 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2139
msgid ""
"If a foreign unit is alone on a tile, you may attempt to bribe it with your "
"Diplomat. By paying a sum of gold the unit will immediately become yours. "
"The exact sum depends on the status of the unit and that of the civilization "
"owning it. However, units belonging to Democratic governments cannot be "
"bribed. Bribery when not at war will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1276 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1983
msgid ""
"Diplomats can also perform a number of actions in another player's city, "
"although each Diplomat may attempt only one action. Most of these actions "
"have a chance of failure. Also, any enemy Diplomats or Spies in the city "
"will oppose hostile actions. In this case, either your unit or the defending "
"unit will die. If the defending unit dies, you lose one movement point and "
"may try again."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1283 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1990
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2264 data/classic/units.ruleset:2055
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2082 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2154
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2800 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2336
msgid "The actions available to Diplomats in a city are:"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1285 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1992
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2057 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2084
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2156 data/royale/units.ruleset:2802
msgid ""
" - \"Establish Embassy\": This action always succeeds, and gives permanent "
"contact with the city's owner, as well as intelligence on their national "
"budget and technology."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1289 data/civ2/units.ruleset:1996
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2272 data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2499
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2061 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2088
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2160 data/royale/units.ruleset:2806
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2344 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2575
msgid ""
" - \"Investigate City\": Your unit attempts to report detailed information "
"about the city: its status, what buildings and units are within, and what it "
"is currently producing."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1293 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2000
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2276 data/classic/units.ruleset:2065
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2092 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2164
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2810 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2348
msgid ""
" - \"Sabotage City\": Your unit attempts either to disrupt all the city's "
"work so far towards its current project, or to destroy an existing building "
"in the city, at random. Once built, Palaces and Wonders cannot be sabotaged, "
"and attempts to sabotage City Walls or any building in a capital each halve "
"the chance of success. Sabotage may only be attempted when openly at war."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1300 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2007
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2283 data/classic/units.ruleset:2072
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2099 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2171
#: data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2355
msgid ""
" - \"Steal Technology\": Your unit attempts to learn the secrets of a random "
"technology known to the city's owner but not to you. Technology may only be "
"stolen once from a given enemy city by Diplomats. This action may be "
"attempted even when not at war, but will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1306 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2013
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2078 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2105
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2177
msgid ""
" - \"Incite a Revolt\": In return for gold a foreign city will change "
"allegiance and join your empire, bringing along all nearby units that call "
"it home, but reducing its size by 1. Units in other cities remain in the "
"enemy's control, but units outside cities are lost to both players. The "
"exact sum depends on the status of the city and that of the civilization "
"that owns it. It is not possible to incite a rebellion in a capital, or in "
"any city governed by a democracy. Incitement may be attempted in peacetime, "
"but will cause a diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1316 data/classic/units.ruleset:2088
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2115 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2187
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2827 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2371
msgid ""
"In some game strategies, hordes of Diplomats can be used to wreak havoc on "
"the enemy. Little wonder that Diplomats are often viewed with suspicion and "
"fear!"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1323 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2090
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2380 data/classic/units.ruleset:2168
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2195 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2267
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3101 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2455
msgid "Caravan"
msgstr "karavan"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1349 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2116
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2194 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2221
msgid ""
"A Caravan carries goods or material for trading with distant cities and "
"foreign countries, or to help build wonders in your cities."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1352
msgid ""
"Caravans can establish trade routes with your own cities or those of other "
"nations (even enemies) by traveling to them. A route's ongoing revenue is "
"doubled if the two cities involved are on different continents, and doubled "
"again if the cities are from different civilizations. This last condition "
"means the net benefit to your civilization of a trade route is the same "
"regardless of whether you own both cities or only one of them. If you only "
"own one city, trade in each city is doubled, but you only get the benefit "
"from one end of the route. Each city can support a maximum of three trade "
"routes."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1362 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2129
#: data/classic/units.ruleset:2210 data/experimental/units.ruleset:2237
msgid ""
"Every Caravan that is used to build a wonder will add 50 shields towards the "
"production of the wonder."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1365 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2132
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2421 data/classic/units.ruleset:2213
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2240 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2299
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3139 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2497
msgid ""
"TIP: You can stockpile a stack of Caravans in advance and bring them all "
"into a city where you have started to build a wonder, and finish it in only "
"one turn!"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1372 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2202
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2547 data/classic/units.ruleset:2324
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2356 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2411
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3270 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2623
msgid "Barbarian Leader"
msgstr "barbarhövding"

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1398 data/civ2/units.ruleset:2228
#: data/civ2civ3/units.ruleset:2580 data/classic/units.ruleset:2357
#: data/experimental/units.ruleset:2389 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:2444
#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3303 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2656
msgid ""
"One Barbarian Leader appears every time there is a barbarian uprising "
"somewhere in the world."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/units.ruleset:1401
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When a Barbarian Leader is killed on a tile without any defending units, the "
"100 gold ransom is paid, but only to land units."
msgstr ""
"En barbarhövding dyker upp varje gång det sker ett barbaruppror någonstans i "
"världen.\n"
"\n"
"När en barbarhövding dödas på en ruta utan försvarstrupper, betalas 100 guld "
"ut i lösen, men endast till marktrupper."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:65 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:65
#: data/classic/buildings.ruleset:65 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:67
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:64 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:65
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:65
msgid "Airport"
msgstr "flygplats"

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:81
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Allows a city to produce veteran air units (including helicopters) and "
"missiles. Also, damaged air units (including helicopters) which stay in town "
"for one full turn without moving are completely restored."
msgstr ""
"Gör det möjligt att bygga erfarna marina enheter i staden. Dessutom "
"återställs skadade marina enheter som vilar i staden en hel omgång "
"fullständigt."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:86 data/experimental/buildings.ruleset:88
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:85
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Two cities with Airports can airlift one unit per turn. Airlifting instantly "
"transports the unit from one city to another and will use all of the unit's "
"movement points. A unit must have some movement points left to be airlifted."
msgstr ""
"Gör det möjligt att bygga erfaret stridsflyg i staden. Dessutom lagas "
"skadade stridsflygplan som stannar en hel omgång utan att röra sig, helt.\n"
"\n"
"Två städer med flygplatser kan flygfrakta en trupp varje omgång. Flygfrakt "
"flyttar omedelbart truppen från den ena staden till den andra och förbrukar "
"truppens samtliga drag. En trupp måste ha drag kvar för att kunna "
"flygfraktas."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:110 data/classic/buildings.ruleset:110
#: data/multiplayer/buildings.ruleset:136
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Allows a city to grow larger than size 8. A Sewer System is also required "
"for a city to grow larger than size 12."
msgstr ""
"Gör det möjligt för en stad att växa sig större än storlek 8. Ett "
"avloppssystem kommer att krävas för att en stad skall kunna växa sig större "
"än storlek 12."

#: data/civ2/buildings.ruleset:158 data/civ2civ3/buildings.ruleset:238
