msgstr ""
"Nybyggare och ingenjörer har förmågan att förändra landskapet i rutor på "
"flera sätt."

#: data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1427
msgid ""
"Fortresses improve defense for land units outside cities. Among other "
"effects, a land unit remaining in a fortress for a whole turn without moving "
"recovers a quarter of its hitpoints. With Invention, fortresses gain "
"watchtowers from which land units can see further afield."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1544 data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1521
#: data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1516
msgid ""
"Building roads on river tiles requires knowledge of Bridge Building. City "
"center tiles automatically get roads (unless they are on a river tile and "
"you do not yet know Bridge Building)."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1603 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1575
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any land terrain type may have a River on it. A River adds 1 trade to the "
"resources produced by that tile. It also increases a tile's defense factor "
"by 50%. Finally, land units may move along a River (but not diagonally) for "
"fast travel."
msgstr ""
"Varje terrängtyp (utom hav) kan genomkorsas av en flod. En flod lägger 1 "
"handel till tillgångarna som utvinns på den rutan. Den ökar även rutans "
"försvarsfaktor med 50%. Slutligen kan marktrupper följa floder (dock inte "
"diagonalt); förflyttningar längs floder kostar bara 1/3 drag.\n"
"\n"
"Vägar och järnvägar kan endast byggas på rutor med flod av civilisationer "
"som lärt sig teknologin brobyggnad."

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:480 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:480
msgid ""
"Settlers can also perform most of the same terrain alterations as Workers "
"(but cannot build Airbases or Buoys)."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:525 data/experimental/units.ruleset:542
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:526
msgid ""
"Workers can build airbases and buoys, which Settlers cannot. Workers must be "
"on board a ship to build buoys."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:563 data/experimental/units.ruleset:585
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:564
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Engineers are similar to Workers, but they work twice as fast and move twice "
"as fast. Engineers may also perform major terrain transformations which are "
"beyond the capabilities of Workers and Settlers, such as converting Tundra "
"into Desert, or even Ocean into Swamp in some circumstances (when on board "
"an ocean-going vessel, on a tile surrounded by sufficient existing land). "
"See the Terrain Alterations section for more details."
msgstr ""
"Ingenjörer liknar arbetare men de arbetar och förflyttar sig dubbelt så "
"fort. Ingenjörer kan även utföra större landskapsförändringar (till exempel "
"omvandling av tundra till öken) vilket är mer än vad arbetarna förmår.\n"
"\n"
"TIPS 1:  Byt om möjligt ut arbetare mot ingenjörer eftersom ingenjörer "
"förbrukar lika mycket tillgångar som arbetare.\n"
"\n"
"TIPS 2:  Om man lyckas färdigställa Leonardos verkstad, så försök forska "
"fram sprängämnen innan Leonardos verkstad blir omodern. På så sätt ersätts "
"ens arbetare utan kostnad."

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:571 data/experimental/units.ruleset:593
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:572
msgid ""
"TIP 1: Upgrade Workers to Engineers when possible, as Engineers require the "
"same resources as ordinary Workers."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:574 data/experimental/units.ruleset:596
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:575
msgid ""
"TIP 2: If you manage to build Leonardo's Workshop, research Explosives "
"before the Workshop becomes obsolete. This way, your Workers units will be "
"upgraded for free."
msgstr ""

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:738 data/experimental/units.ruleset:760
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:739
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Equipped with long pikes, Pikemen replaces Phalanx as the preferred city "
"defender. Mounted units have a disadvantage against Pikemen."
msgstr ""
"Spjutbäraren är utrustad med långa spjut och ersätter falangen som främsta "
"försvarare av städer."

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:808 data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:844
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A number of Partisans are granted free when an enemy conquers your city -- "
"they automatically assume defensive positions in the surrounding countryside "
"-- but only under these conditions:\n"
"\n"
" - Guerilla Warfare must be known by at least one player.\n"
" - You must be the player who originally built the city.\n"
" - You must know about Communism and Gunpowder.\n"
" - You must run either a Democracy or a Communist government."
msgstr ""
"Gerillakrigare strider för sin frihet och utnyttjar terrängen till sin "
"fördel.\n"
"\n"
"Man får ett antal gerillakrigare utan kostnad när man förlorar en stad till "
"fienden, men bara enligt dessa villkor:\n"
"\n"
" - Gerillakrigföring måste vara känt av minst 1 spelare.\n"
"\n"
" - Man måste vara den spelare som ursprungligen grundade staden.\n"
"\n"
" - Man måste känna till kommunism och krut.\n"
"\n"
" - Man måste ha demokrati eller kommunism som statsskick."

#: data/classic/units.ruleset:1342 data/experimental/units.ruleset:1365
#: data/multiplayer/units.ruleset:1442
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fighters are your first airborne units. They can move anywhere and attack "
